   "source": [
    "# ðŸŒ GraphRAG Core: Climate Intelligence Tutorial\n",
    "\n",
    "[![Open In Colab](https://colab.research.google.com/assets/colab-badge.svg)](https://colab.research.google.com/github/nunezmatias/grafoRag/blob/main/graphRagClima/examples/Tutorial_GraphRAG.ipynb)\n",
    "\n",
    "Welcome to the **GraphRAG Core** tutorial. This library comes **pre-loaded** with a massive Climate Adaptation Knowledge Graph, allowing you to perform deep scientific research instantly.\n",
    "\n",
    "### ðŸš€ Features\n",
    "1. **Plug & Play**: No data setup required. The Climate Knowledge Base is embedded.\n",
    "2. **Deep Retrieval**: Finds not just one paper, but the entire context around a topic.\n",
    "3. **Causal Reasoning**: Traverses the graph to find systemic risks (e.g., Heat -> Drought -> Food Insecurity).\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Installation\n",
    "Install the library directly from GitHub. This will also download the embedded database."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!pip install git+https://github.com/nunezmatias/grafoRag.git\n",
    "\n",
    "import os\n",
    "from graphrag_core import GraphRAGEngine\n",
    "print(\"âœ… Library Installed & Loaded\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Initialize the Engine\n",
    "We initialize the engine without arguments. It will automatically detect and load the internal Climate Database."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "engine = GraphRAGEngine()\n",
    "# Output should say: \"Using DEFAULT Internal Vector DB\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Run a Complex Query\n",
    "Let's research **\"Cascading risks of extreme heat\"**.\n",
    "\n",
    "We use:\n",
    "* `top_k=3`: Identify 3 core themes.\n",
    "* `context_k=4`: Read 4 deep-dive papers per theme.\n",
    "* `hops=2`: Traverse 2 levels of causality in the graph."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "query = \"cascading risks of extreme heat and urban floods\"\n",
    "\n",
    "results = engine.search(\n",
    "    query=query, \n",
    "    top_k=3, \n",
    "    context_k=4, \n",
    "    hops=2\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"--- Research Stats ---\")\n",
    "print(f\"Primary Sources: {results['stats']['primary']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Context Expansion: {results['stats']['context']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Causal Links:      {results['stats']['graph']}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Inspect the Intelligence\n",
    "Let's see what the graph found."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 1. Check a Paper\n",
    "p = results['papers'][0]\n",
    "print(f\"ðŸ“„ Top Paper: {p['title']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Snippet: {p['content'][:200]}...\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 2. Check a Causal Chain\n",
    "print(\"ðŸ”— Causal Chains Discovered:\")\n",
    "for link in results['graph_links'][:5]:\n",
    "    print(f\"   {link['source']} --[{link['relation']}]--> {link['target']}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Generate Expert Prompt\n",
    "Finally, we package this intelligence into a prompt for GPT-4."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "prompt = engine.format_prompt(\n",
    "    results,\n",
    "    query,\n",
    "    system_role=\"You are a UN Climate Adaptation Specialist.\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Here is your optimized prompt:\")\n",
    "print(\"==="*20 + \"\"*10 + \"==="*20)\n",
    "print(prompt[:1000] + \"... [Truncated]\")\n",
    "print(\"==="*20 + \"\"*10 + \"==="*20)"
   ]
  }
